15 WHEREAS, he further serves as the vice-president-at-large of the General Missionary
16 Baptist Convention of Georgia and is a certified instructor for the local, state, and national
17 Congress of Christian Education; and
18 WHEREAS, he is a proud member of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity Inc., the Kappa Alpha Psi
19 Columbus Alumni Chapter, the Columbus Georgia Family Connection Coalition, and the 100
20 Black Men of America; and
21 WHEREAS, whether the task is preparing a sermon, visiting the sick, counseling the
22 troubled, baptizing a new believer, or acting as a theologian, educator, administrator, or
23 humanitarian, Reverend Corey J. Neal has shown the energy, devotion, and commitment
24 truly reflective of divine guidance; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper to recognize the outstanding accomplishments
26 of the dynamic Christian ministry of this devout and pious man.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Corey J. Neal on the wonderful
29 occasion of his 17th pastoral anniversary and extend best wishes for many more years of
30 successful fellowship and leadership.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Reverend Corey J. Neal.
